post_text: Citizens Bank of Edinburg President, Mark LeVault, gets approval for a hometown grant to help Edinburg CUSD#4 with COVID relief. The Federal Home Loan Bank of Chicago’s (FHLBank Chicago) Targeted Impact Fund provides member banks with grants to support relief efforts for populations hardest-hit by COVID-19 as well as to promote equity and opportunity. Thank you Mark LeVault and Citizens Bank or Edinburg for continually going above and beyond to support our school.

post_text:
Introducing "Two-minute Tips!" Every week (or maybe more often) we will try to post a short video with advice for Wildcats and their families to help make things easier during remote learning.

Future topics include:
-setting up a good work space
-time management and rewarding yourself for good work!
-getting on a good sleep/wake schedule
-getting in touch with teachers when you have a question
-Google Chrome bookmarks and other tricks

Have an idea for a tip? Having a hard time with something specific and need advice? Drop it in the comments or send a message to Sra Skinner.

Even though we're physically separate, we can all still solve problems together and #EdinburgROAR. Have a great week, Wildcats.

Daily Schedule

Chromebook agreement

Attention all Jr High/High School Students and Parents: Please observe all COVID safety protocols, wear a mask and avoid bringing extra family members into the building if possible.

Bring a backpack

Enter through the cafeteria door (E10)

Stop at the first table as you enter. You will have documents to sign and get the following items at pick up:

Class schedule

Daily Block Schedule

Chromebook agreement

Chromebook carrying case

Chromebook

Textbooks

Students will receive updated usernames and passwords for their Chromebook. Once students return home, they need to login after they pick up their Chromebook to make sure they are able to get logged in. Once logged in, they will need to log into their school email account. There will be invitations to your Google Classrooms. Please join each class and complete the quick assignment that is waiting for you.

Thank you.

Reminder to schedule your child's physical, dental and eye exams. This is for all students who registered whether your students is virtual or in-class learning.
Pre-K needs: Certified Birth Certificate, Physical and Lead screening
Kindergarten needs: Certified Birth Certificate, Physical, Dental and Eye
2nd Grade needs: Dental
6th Grade needs: Physical and Dental
9th Grade needs: Physical and Dental
If your child plans on playing sports grades 5th-12th grade they will also need a sports physical.
All Certified Birth Certificates and Physicals need turned in by October 9, 2020.

John Bryan
June 30 at 6:57 PM ·

Attention Edinburg parents and students. Due to the ongoing issues with the pandemic and with recommendations from the state and the health department, the school has decided that in the students' best interests that we will not hold prom as scheduled. I am sorry about this but the safety of our students is the most important thing. However I have been told that for any member of the class of 2020 who wants to come to prom next year that you will more than welcome. I am also, in the coming days, going to try and get out a poll for the students to still decided on. 2020 prom king and queen. Again sorry for the bad news. Hope everyone is having a great week and has a fantastic 4th of July. #EdinburgROAR

Please take a moment to fill out the 2020 Census survey. We are the tenth lowest town (at 62.1%) out of thirteen in Christian County. Let's see if we can get that percentage up.

Here are links to the online Census and more information:

The 2020 Census is your chance to shape your community—and your future. Learn more at 2020census.gov. You can complete your questionnaire online at: https://2020census.gov Respond by phone or mail too: https://2020census.gov/en/ways-to-respond.html #2020census

Please share this information with your Edinburg friends and family!

post_text:
Students and families:
Governor Pritzker announced this afternoon that the school cancellation would be extended for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. I am sad to hear of the extended school closure, and I am sure you are saddened as well. We are thinking of all of you and hoping that you and your families remain safe and can find joy and peace with each other. We understand that you will have questions and concerns, and we are here for you to answer them as best we can. We know that many experiences have been taken away from you and we wish we could give you those experiences. Remember, we are all in this together! We will get through this.
#EdinburgROAR

post_text: If you'd like to purchase a hat post in comments.
shared_text:
Edinburg - South Fork - Wildcats Basketball
April 4 at 5:48 PM ·

We were recently offered a promotion to buy 48 hats and get 48 free. We thought this was a great avenue to sell some Wildcats merchandise, but more importantly, to give back. We will have the hat in the attached pictures for sale for $20, and all the proceeds will be donated to Coaches vs. COVID-19. Please send a message on here if you are interested. Since it is limited supply, it will be first come, first serve. Payment will be required up front so we can get straight to donating to the cause, and then I will deliver the hats when they come in in the most safe and sanitized way as possible at that current time. post_text:
Thank you to all our staff, parents, and students for working diligently and patiently through this learning at home process. We have been experiencing many problems with the proxy server. Our QNS tech representative is working on several issues. You may experience a short period without user access as he tries to problem solve and correct issues. In the meantime, here are a few trouble-shooting ideas you could try if you are experiencing problems with your device.

1. log in to your computer (JH & HS) as you have previously done at school, then use the new username and password when the proxy box pops up.

2. Close all tabs, then log out and log back in.

3. Press Ctrl+Shift+Backspace, then in the drop down menu select All Time, then Clear all at the bottom of the box. Once you have completed this step, log out of everything, then log back in.

I hope everyone is enjoying time with family and staying healthy.

⭐️ Stacy Kurlakowsky is a Star Student. ⭐️ She is a Sophomore and the daughter of Mike Kurlakowsky and Deanna Lloyd. She enjoys riding four wheelers and hanging out with friends. Her favorite thing about school is FFA.

These are the comments from Stacy’s teachers:

Mr. Johnson: Stacy is a very good student! She does well with her grades and has a great attitude.

Mr. Bryan: Stacy does her work constantly in a class that can be very distracting to some students and maintains a good attitude and grades.

Mrs. Siemer: Stacy works hard on anything she sets her mind to both in school and FFA, she sets high goals for herself and is determined to achieve them, she is constantly looking for ways she can improve herself and she is always willing to lend a helping hand to others.

Ms. Capranica: Stacy is a wonderful student! She works so hard and is so kind to everyone. Her smile is contagious and she is a joy to have in class!

Way to go Stacy!! 👏🏼 ⭐️

post_text: Today Mrs.Bratcher's 5th grade class had "Market Day"! Students had been earning money since we came back from winter break by doing their classroom jobs, keeping their desk cleaned, earning A+s on tests and more! Students created and ran their own business as we learned about economics and how running a business works. The kids made advertisements, shop signs, had to buy a business license, and created items to sell all on their own! Today our businesses came together and our teachers and the 4th grade class got to shop and purchase our class' items. 5th grade had a lot of fun shopping and selling today and those who came to shop did too!

post_text:
Class of 2023 would like to say Thank you!

#EdinburgROAR
shared_text:
Sra Skinner
February 19 at 1:09 PM ·

THANK YOU EDINBURG COMMUNITY!
The class of 2023 thanks you for participating in the basket raffle and the 50/50 raffle at Friday's basketball game. Congrats to all the winners!

And on a personal note, señora Skinner (me) is so thankful to everyone. I am new to the small-town life and have never seen people come together like they do around here! Thank you for supporting my students (who I LOVE) but also helping me learn so much every day!
I never raised money for things as a student or at the other schools where I've worked. I never took a senior trip - too hard with a class of 560! I never built a float for a parade. I never had a "labor day" celebration. So many things are new to me and I'm loving it.

So; thank you parents, students, admin, and community for being patient with me as I learn to host events and fundraisers. It's out of my wheelhouse and I learn so much every time I do something new. MUCHAS GRACIAS to everyone!
#EdinburgROAR #lifelonglearner #grateful
